    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Men's stiff, round-crowned hats, usually of felt, the large brim cocked or rolled up against the crown; worn from the 17th century.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
